Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/7/00 1:07:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .....</span><hr size=1> well, why use it? if you have to switch it between another weapon anytime you arent in a group with an enchanter? i dont think its a good weapon anyways :P use somethin else that you can use all the time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Quemn Wyndrunner<br>
52 Bard<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/7/00 5:48:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .....</span><hr size=1> Matter of taste I guess - if I'm needed for crowd control (fairly rare now, to be honest) I've usually got an instrument in my hands for charm or (/shudder) mez. If it's an instrument I'm not otherwise using, at least a quick change from drum (eg) to flute is quite possible, and easier than two weapons to flute.<br>
<br>
The thread was about weapons for approx Lv 35, and I started using an ugly stick  quite late (mainly cos at the time I felt that CHA was sacred &quot;whenever&quot; - latterly I just carry the right jewellery with me in case I need to impress mobs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) - about 30th I guess. There are better weapons available, but it's certainly a cheap option at 35th if you're going for a &quot;staff&quot; look.<br>
<br>
Generally I carry three weapons at any time: 1HB, 1HS, piercing. Each has different procs or stats and I change between them fairly regularly, depending on the situation.  <p><b>Brinklith Rioghbhardan</b> - Jester of Avalon<br>
